*{{flagIOC|BLR|2010 Winter|1}}\n*{{flagIOC|CAN|2010 Winter|15}}\n*{{flagIOC|CHN|2010 Winter|14}}\n*{{flagIOC|CZE|2010 Winter|2}}\n*{{flagIOC|DEN|2010 Winter|1}}\n*{{flagIOC|FIN|2010 Winter|4}}\n*{{flagIOC|FRA|2010 Winter|2}}\n*{{flagIOC|GER|2010 Winter|13}}\n*{{flagIOC|ITA|2010 Winter|5}}\n*{{flagIOC|JPN|2010 Winter|19}}\n{{col-2-of-2}}\n*{{flagIOC|KAZ|2010 Winter|4}}\n*{{flagIOC|LAT|2010 Winter|1}}\n*{{flagIOC|NED|2010 Winter|19}}\n*{{flagIOC|NZL|2010 Winter|1}}\n*{{flagIOC|PRK|2010 Winter|1}}\n*{{flagIOC|NOR|2010 Winter|8}}\n*{{flagIOC|POL|2010 Winter|10}}\n*{{flagIOC|RUS|2010 Winter|17}}\n*{{flagIOC|KOR|2010 Winter|16}}\n*{{flagIOC|SWE|2010 Winter|3}}\n*{{flagIOC|SUI|2010 Winter|1}}\n*{{flagIOC|USA|2010 Winter|18}}\n{{col end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110524030733/http://corporate.olympics.com.au/files/96/ISU_speedskating_sum_January08.pdf Qualification System]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110724083429/http://isu.sportcentric.net/db//files/serve.php?id=1482 Qualification times]\n* [http://www.vancouver2010.com/dl/00/44/31/-/44312/prop=data/o1kl3j/44312.pdf Vancouver 2010 Olympic Winter Games Competition Schedule v12]\n\n{{Events at the 2010 Winter Olympics}}\n{{Speed skating at the Winter Olympics}}\n\n[[Category:Speed skating at the Winter Olympics|2010]]\n[[Category:2010 Winter Olympics events]]\n[[Category:2010 in speed skating|O]]\n[[Category:Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics]]\n[[Category:International speed skating competitions hosted by Canada|Olympics, 2010]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{short description|Speed skating at the Olympics}}\n{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Speed skating\n|games = 2010 Winter\n|image = Speed skating pictogram.svg\n|image_size = 100px\n|venue = [[Richmond Olympic Oval]]\n|dates = 13\u201327 February 2010\n|num_events = 12\n|competitors = 177\n|nations = 24\n|prev = [[Speed skating at the 2006 Winter Olympics|2006]]\n|next = [[Speed skating at the 2014 Winter Olympics|2014]]\n}}\n{{Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics}}\n'''[[Speed skating at the Winter Olympics|Speed skating]] at the [[2010 Winter Olympics]]''' was held at the [[Richmond Olympic Oval]], [[Richmond, British Columbia]], between 13 and 27 February 2010.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/winter/2010/SSK/ |title=Speed Skating at the 2010 Vancouver Winter Games |work=Sports Reference |accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n[[Haralds Silovs]] became the first athlete in Olympic history to participate in both [[Short track speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics|short track]] (1500 m) and long track (5000 m) speed skating, and the first to compete in two different disciplines on the same day. He competed in the 5000 m and then raced across town to the 1500 m event. The low altitude of [[Vancouver]] and high humidity inside the [[Richmond Olympic Oval]], set just 3 metres above the sea, meant that no world records in speed skating would be set at these Games.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Toronto Star|url=http://olympics.thestar.com/2010/article/765257--latvia-s-quick-change-artist-makes-olympic-history|title=Latvia's quick-change artist makes Olympic history|date=14 February 2010|accessdate=18 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/02/13/AR2010021303005.html|title=Latvian speedskater is 1st to do double duty|first=Beth|last=Harris|date=13 February 2010|accessdate=18 February 2010}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=New York Times|url=http://vancouver2010.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/02/13/from-long-track-to-short-track-an-unprecedented-task|title=From Long Track to Short Track, an Unprecedented Journey|first=Karen|last=Crouse|date=13 February 2010|accessdate=18 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=CTV Olympics|url=http://www.ctvolympics.ca/speed-skating/news/newsid=41186.html|title=Latvian skater makes Olympic history|author=Agence France Presse|date=14 February 2010|accessdate=18 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/31/sports/olympics/31skate.html|title=Crosstown Ride to a Speedskating First|author=Associated Press|date=30 January 2010|accessdate=18 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Medal summary ==\n\n=== Medal table ===\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = flagIOCteam\n | event          = 2010 Winter\n | team           = \n | gold_KOR = 3 | silver_KOR = 2 | bronze_KOR = 0\n | gold_NED = 3 | silver_NED = 1 | bronze_NED = 3\n | gold_CAN = 2 | silver_CAN = 1 | bronze_CAN = 2\n | gold_CZE = 2 | silver_CZE = 0 | bronze_CZE = 1\n | gold_GER = 1 | silver_GER = 3 | bronze_GER = 0\n | gold_USA = 1 | silver_USA = 2 | bronze_USA = 1\n | gold_JPN = 0 | silver_JPN = 2 | bronze_JPN = 1\n | gold_RUS = 0 | silver_RUS = 1 | bronze_RUS = 1\n | gold_CHN = 0 | silver_CHN = 0 | bronze_CHN = 1\n | gold_NOR = 0 | silver_NOR = 0 | bronze_NOR = 1\n | gold_POL = 0 | silver_POL = 0 | bronze_POL = 1\n}}\n\n=== Men's events ===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|columns=2}}\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| 500 metres <br />{{DetailsLink|Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 500 metres}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Results of the 2010 Olympic Winter Games 500 meters Men|url=http://www.speedskatingstats.com/index.php?file=championships&g=m&type=og&event=500&year=2010|publisher=SpeedSkatingStats.com|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Mo Tae-bum]]|KOR|2010 Winter}}||69.82\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Keiichiro Nagashima]]|JPN|2010 Winter}}||69.98\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Joji Kato]]|JPN|2010 Winter}}||70.01\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| 1000 metres <br />{{DetailsLink|Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 1000 metres}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Results of the 2010 Olympic Winter Games 1000 meters Men|url=http://www.speedskatingstats.com/index.php?file=championships&g=m&type=og&event=1000&year=2010|publisher=SpeedSkatingStats.com|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Shani Davis]]|USA|2010 Winter}}||1:08.94\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Mo Tae-bum]]|KOR|2010 Winter}}||1:09.12 \n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Chad Hedrick]]|USA|2010 Winter}}||1:09.32\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| 1500 metres <br />{{DetailsLink|Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 1500 metres}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Results of the 2010 Olympic Winter Games 1500 meters Men|url=http://www.speedskatingstats.com/index.php?file=championships&g=m&type=og&event=1500&year=2010|publisher=SpeedSkatingStats.com|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Mark Tuitert]]|NED|2010 Winter}}||1:45.57\n| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[Shani Davis]]|USA|2010 Winter}}||1:46.10\n| {{flagIOCmedalist|[[H\u00e5vard B\u00f8kko]]|NOR|2010 Winter}}||1:46.13\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| 5000 metres <br />{{DetailsLink|Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Results of the 2010 Olympic Winter Games 5000 meters Men|url=http://www.speedskatingstats.com/index.php?file=championships&g=m&type=og&event=5000&year=2010|publisher=SpeedSkatingStats.com|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Sven Kramer]]|NED|2010 Winter}} ||6:14.60 ''[[List of Olympic records in speed skating|OR]]''\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Lee Seung-hoon]]|KOR|2010 Winter}}||6:16.95\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Ivan Skobrev]]|RUS|2010 Winter}} || 6:18.05\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| 10000 metres <br />{{DetailsLink|Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 10000 metres}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Results of the 2010 Olympic Winter Games 10,000 meters Men|url=http://www.speedskatingstats.com/index.php?file=championships&g=m&type=og&event=10000&year=2010|publisher=SpeedSkatingStats.com|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Lee Seung-hoon]]|KOR|2010 Winter}}||12:58.55 ''[[List of Olympic records in speed skatin