ckert]]|GER|2010 Winter}}||6:51.39\n|{{flagIOCmedalist|[[Clara Hughes]]|CAN|2010 Winter}}||6:55.73\n|-valign=\"top\"\n| Team pursuit <br />{{DetailsLink|Speed skating at the 2010 Winter Olympics \u2013 Women's team pursuit}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Results of the 2010 Olympic Winter Games Team pursuit Women|url=http://www.speedskatingstats.com/index.php?file=championships&g=w&type=og&event=team&year=2010|publisher=SpeedSkatingStats.com|accessdate=19 November 2013}}</ref>\n|valign=top| {{flagIOCteam|GER|2010 Winter}}<br />[[Daniela Ansch\u00fctz-Thoms]]<br />[[Stephanie Beckert]]<br />''[[Anni Friesinger-Postma]]''*<br />[[Katrin Mattscherodt]]|| 3:02.82\n|valign=top| {{flagIOCteam|JPN|2010 Winter}}<br />[[Masako Hozumi]]<br />[[Nao Kodaira]]<br />[[Maki Tabata]]|| 3:02.84\n|valign=top| {{flagIOCteam|POL|2010 Winter}}<br />[[Katarzyna Bachleda-Curu\u015b]]<br />[[Katarzyna Wo\u017aniak]]<br />[[Luiza Z\u0142otkowska]]|| 3:03.73\n|}\n<nowiki>*</nowiki> Skater who did not participate in the final, but received a medal.\n\n== Events ==\nA total of twelve speed skating events were held at Vancouver 2010:\n\n{| class=wikitable\n! Men !! Women\n|-\n| 500 m || 500 m\n|-\n| 1000 m || 1000 m\n|-\n| 1500 m || 1500 m\n|-\n| 5000 m || 3000 m\n|-\n| 10000 m || 5000 m\n|-\n| Team pursuit || Team pursuit\n|}\n\n== Competition schedule ==\n<small>All times are [[Pacific Time Zone|Pacific Standard Time]] ([[UTC-8]]).</small>\n\n{| class=wikitable\n! Day !! Date !! Start !! Finish !! Event !! Phase\n|- \n| Day 2 || Saturday, 13 February 2010|| 12:00 || 14:20 ||colspan=2| '''5000 m men'''\n|-\n| Day 3 || Sunday, 14 February 2010 || 13:00 || 14:50 ||colspan=2| '''3000 m women'''\n|-\n| Day 4 || Monday, 15 February 2010|| 15:30 || 18:50 ||colspan=2| '''500 m men'''\n|-\n| Day 5 || Tuesday, 16 February 2010|| 13:00 || 16:05 ||colspan=2| '''500 m women'''\n|-\n| Day 6 || Wednesday, 17 February 2010|| 16:00 || 17:30 ||colspan=2| '''1000 m men'''\n|-\n| Day 7 || Thursday, 18 February 2010|| 13: